TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bucovetsky, Sam
T1  - Price Dispersion and Stockpiling by Consumers
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/07/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297675
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 50
IS  - 3
SP  - 443
EP  - 465
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper presents a model of equilibrium price dispersion in which buyers do not search. However they are able to store the non-durable commodity for future use. Such behaviour implies sellers' demand curves are endogenously generated by the observed price distribution. Equilibrium is shown to exist. Although more than one price may be charged in equilibrium, the monopoly price will occur with positive probability. Comparative static results are derived with a linear version of the model, some of which are “perverse”.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297675
ER  - 



