TY  - JOUR
AU  - Anderson, Gordon
AU  - Blundell, Richard
T1  - Testing Restrictions in a Flexible Dynamic Demand System: An Application to Consumers' Expenditure in Canada
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/07/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297672
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 50
IS  - 3
SP  - 397
EP  - 410
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Traditionally, restrictions on systems of demand equations have been tested using static models, whilst being estimated with time series data. This paper develops a vector time series model of expenditure shares in the context of a singular dynamic demand system. The model allows for non-symmetric and non-homogeneous short run behaviour. The homogeneity and symmetry restrictions are only examined in the long run structure. Results based on Canadian time series data are presented and reject the current practise of static modelling while restrictions suggested by economic theory are not rejected when imposed on the long run structure.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297672
ER  - 



